description: Get ready to swing into action with our Swing Series! Led by expert instructor Kat Single-Dain, and often featuring awesome lead Laz Savic, our classes cover a variety of styles including charleston, lindy hop, and vernacular jazz. This series is for Beginners AND those who have taken our series or other beginner series before!! We will be giving individual attention to folks in order to challenge everyone -- great for those who have taken either none, one or two of Kat's series before. This series of 6 weekly classes begins on September and takes place every Friday for a total of six classes from 6-7pm. We will usually play music from 7-730pm at the space after your lesson so that you can stay and practice! Cost: $120, and includes free entrance to one of our monthly dances, which happens right after the lesson on September 26th in this case!

description: Maureen Washington is the Winner of the 2014 Black Canadian Award for Best Jazz and Soul Artist! A consummate performer, she slips easily from sassy to sexy within a single line of lyrics, at times echoing the haunting tones of Etta James and Carmen McRae, then faster than the mind and ear can make the transition, Maureen Washington exudes the impish irreverence of Jann Arden and the vocal agility of Holly Cole. With all splendor attached to such comparisons, Maureen’s musical style remains distinctly her own. Her vocal diversity lends itself to performances of blues, swing jazz and funk , and her versatile repertoire, ranges from classics to lively originals. It's been a while since we've presented Maureen, her shows are usually sold out, so make sure to get your tickets in advance! Tickets are also available at Oak Bay Recreation Centre reception, 1975 Bee Street, in person, or by phone 250-595-7946.
location: Upstairs Lounge, Oak Bay Recreation Centre 1975 Bee Street Oak Bay, BC V8R 5E6

event_name: SLOW DANCE SPEED DATING! - up to 40, Hetero Edition, W seek M Tickets
description: Welcome to 'Slow Dance Speed Dating at Gloria's Happy Hour,' brought to you by the almost famous but definitely infamous Gloria. Gloria, our charming host, is not your average matchmaker. She's a former chorus girl turned relationship guru with a penchant for humor and a taste for delightful libations. Gloria puts a massive twist on traditional speed dating. You might make friends, or perhaps find something more special – it's all about savouring the moment and doing something uniquely fun. Worried about striking up conversations? Fear not! In this friendly and relaxed atmosphere, you'll discover connections you never expected while swaying to the music beneath the glimmering disco ball. Worried about your dance skills? No need! This isn't a race; it's a casual, unhurried shuffle to the rhythm of your heart. Let the music be your guide, and if all else fails, just blame it on the music and/or Gloria. This link is for women Seeking men. You can also etransfer $25 directly to dustyflowerpotcabaret@gmail.com to join and save on fees! Note this event is for this age group: UP TO 40ish. You can absolutely come if you fall outside the lines but at least you know the general bracket of the group! Mark your calendar for an unforgettable event at the Dusty Flowerpot Cabaret. Doors and bar open at 7:30 pm and the dating starts at 8 pm. This is THE HETERO EDITION of the event (in all cases the gender referred to is self-identified). At The Dusty Flowerpot Cabaret, we celebrate love and inclusivity. Whether you're single, coupled up, or just looking for a good time, we've saved a spot for you. Put on your dancing shoes and prepare for an evening filled with laughter and surprises, courtesy of The Dusty Flowerpot Cabaret's talented crew. Whether you find a soulmate, simply a new partner in crime, or in dire need to be entertained, you're in for an unforgettable night.
location: The Dusty Flowerpot Cabaret, 2050 Scotia Street Vancouver, BC V5T 4T1

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Victoria Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9, Canada

source: Victoria International Kizomba Festival 6th: SENSUAL EDITION
location: Ukrainian Cultural Centre, 3277 Douglas St., Victoria, BC

event_name: Free Outdoor Intro Dance Class + Social
description: Join us for an introduction to Kizomba with Aaron and Fernanda— part of our summer series, proudly sponsored by the City of Victoria! Every Monday | June–August 5:30–7:30 PM 1.5-hour dance class followed by a 30-minute outdoor social. Dance style rotates monthly. This free outdoor event is open to everyone — no partner or dance experience needed. All ages, bodies, and abilities are warmly welcomed! Whether you’re dancing the night away or soaking in the summer vibes, come be part of this vibrant community celebration. Don’t forget to bring a water bottle and come ready to move!
source: Victoria International Kizomba Festival 6th: SENSUAL EDITION
location: Ship's Point Inner Harbour, Big Blue Sailing, Victoria, BC V8W, Canada

description: Dancing brings us together—one smile, one step, one friendship at a time. Want to join us in celebrating connection, culture, and community? The VLDA has been invited by the @vihns.bc to participate in the Victoria Day Parade on Monday, May 19th, taking turns social dancing behind a decorated vehicle, sharing smiles and handing out flyers for Latin dance organizations like the @victorialatindanceassociation , @bachatavictoria , and more. If you’d like to be part of this and promote your classes or events, or just to bring more people into our amazing community, please send us a message by the end of the day May 7, so we can include you in the roster! You can participate in social dancing or just handing out flyers and walking by the vehicle, or both!
source: Victoria International Kizomba Festival 6th: SENSUAL EDITION
location: Downtown Victoria, Victoria

event_name: Sunday Sundown Social: Fire and Ice
description: Celebrate the arrival of spring with us on Sunday, May 25th, 2025, for an evening of Latin social dancing with our fire and ice theme! Come dressed in your favorite red or blue colors and you’ll be entered into a raffle for a chance to win a special prize. Event Schedule: Doors Open: 4:15 PM Beginner Dance Lesson: 4:30 PM - 5:00 PM The dance style varies each month. Social Dancing: 5:00 PM - 8:30 PM Join us in James Bay at 111 Superior Street, where we’ll be heating things up with Salsa, Bachata, Kizomba, and Merengue. Although song requests aren’t taken during the event, you’re welcome to share your favorite tunes in our WhatsApp community group beforehand, and we’ll consider them for our playlist. Admission: $15 for General Admission $12 for Students with a valid ID We accept debit, credit, or cash (cash preferred). Please note that a small fee applies for debit or credit transactions. This event is open to everyone—no partner or previous dance experience is required. All ages, bodies, and abilities are warmly welcomed! Whether you’re dancing the night away or simply enjoying the spring spirit, everyone is invited to be part of this vibrant community event. Don’t forget to bring a water bottle to stay hydrated throughout the evening. Monthly Events: This event is part of our ongoing series held on the last Sunday of every month from September to May. Make sure to mark your calendars! As a community collective non-profit association, we truly value your continuous support. All funds are reinvested to improve the quality of our gatherings and to create even more memorable experiences for you. It costs approximately $4,000 to run basic events for the year, covering costs like insurance, permits, equipment, venue rentals, administration, and website maintenance. Disclaimer: Please be aware that videos and photos may be taken during our events and could be posted on social media or online later. We appreciate your understanding!
source: Victoria International Kizomba Festival 6th: SENSUAL EDITION
location: 111 Superior St, Victoria, BC V8V 1T2, Canada
price: $15 for General Admission, $12 for Students with a valid ID

Sunday, 18th 11am-12pm solo technique all levels. 12.30pm-1.30pm for couples only. Per person: $20 / technique class $25/ partnered workshop $80 entire weekend. Next workshop dates are June 21st & 22nd.

description: Chris was the first to introduce Salsa to Nanaimo. For many years he was teaching and running socials, which I, and many other dancers from Courtenay went to RELIGIOUSLY. Chris had a big part in why I love salsa so much. His classes are always fun, and he has so much to offer as a dance teacher. It's great seeing the latin dance community grow with the help of Leon , Emily , and many other teachers before them, and I know Chris will only be adding more value to it. Even if you're not a beginner anymore, I highly recommend you try his classes. Take advantage of this great opportunity!
source: For those of you who don't know Chris, let me tell you something ...

description: FREE community event weekly in June! Downtown Duncan Wednesday evenings starting at 6:30pm The evening starts off with a beginner swing dance class (come early). After the class we’ll played recorded music for social dancing until things get quiet or 8:30pm, whichever comes first. Come with friends or to make friends! Fair weather event only, check Harbour City Swing socials for updates The best way to support local events like these is to: 1) come out 2) share with people who might like these events 3) bring people out to these event with you It's more impactful and we'd prefer not to fill the pockets of Zuckerberg or other billionaires (via META advertising)
location: Duncan City Hall 200 Craig Street, Duncan

event_name: A Weekend Workshop of Milonguero Style Tango with Liz Haight
description: Come for an experiential and exploratory weekend of Milonguero Style Tango with Liz Haight! This 5 class 3 day workshop plus milonga is open to intermediate and advanced Tango dancers.
location: The Abbey, Cumberland, Vancouver Island, BC

event_name: Victoria WCS Collective Beginner Lesson and Social Dancing

Also, no partner necessary, we got you! Please bring indoor scuff-free dance shoes or socks to dance in.
location: 2750 Quadra St # 111, Victoria, British Columbia

event_name: Victoria West Coast Swing Collective social dance
description: Victoria West Coast Swing Collective social dance. Door opens at 7:30pm. DJ's in the comments. Beginners are welcome. No partner is required. There will NOT be a beginner lesson, but if you're brand new, let the person at the door know and they'll find someone to teach you the starter steps. Dance shoes or socks on the dance floor only. Bring your own water. No food or drink (except water) in the dance area by request of the hall. If you bring a snack to keep your energy up, please enjoy it in the foyer.
location: 3255 Harriet RD, VICTORIA, BC, V8Z3S3, CA

event_name: Saturday Beginner Lesson and Social Dance at Eastern Star Hall
description: Doors open at 6:45 pm. Beginner lesson by John de Pfyffer from 7 to 8 pm. Social dancing from 8 to 10:15 pm. No need to register and no dance experience or partner required. Please bring scuff-free indoor dance shoes with low heels (or socks) to dance in and a water bottle.

event_name: Texture Your Moves for West Coast Swing
description: This workshop focuses on practical musicality and movement drills to enhance your West Coast Swing patterns. Learn to add styling, preserve partnership connection, and enjoy being musical with various partners. The workshop will help you level up your musicality by adding body pulse and groove to your basic patterns, making your social dancing more creative and personalized. The event is limited to 14 people and no partner is required.

description: Lindy hop classes on the Coast! Rhythm City brings a passion for Swing dancing, a safe, fun, and inclusive learning culture, and over two decades of experience dancing and teaching. We'll have weekly classes on Tuesdays starting in April, and we're kicking things off with a weekend intensive for beginners: and introduction to Swing and partner dancing like no other! If you’ve never danced before, or maybe tried it out but never felt like you quite got it, this weekend’s beginner classes are for you! Get great instruction in a condensed intensive format. Start off slow and easy, practice, and meet other new Swing dancers. Saturday, April 13 and Sunday April 14 at the Kinsmen Hall in Dougall Park, Lower Gibsons from noon-4pm each day. Close to the public market and marina for re-fueling and getting a breather between classes. 12-1pm Instruction 1-1:30pm coaching/break 1:30-2:30pm Instruction 2:30-3pm coaching/break 3-4pm Instruction Sunday only: 4-5pm social dance/practice/mingle If this weekend doesn't work for you, or you're looking for weekly classes, we'll be running beginner classes on Tuesday evenings at the Kinsmen Hall, starting April 23.
location: Kinsmen Hall Dougall Park, Lower Gibsons

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Learn to Dance Salsa and Bachata - First Class Free
description: Ready to get your hips moving, feet stomping, and heart pumping to the rollicking rhythms of la música latina? Whether you're a complete newbie or just looking to sharpen your skills, our fun and friendly classes will have you grooving in no time. Bonus : Your first class is absolutely free! Feel the energy, embrace the music, and unleash the dancer within! No partner? No problem—you’ll meet new friends while learning new moves. Two left feet? Don’t worry! We’ll have you grooving with confidence before you know it, and wondering why you didn’t start sooner.
location: 345 West Broadway Vancouver, BC V5Y 1P8
price: First class free; Salsa or Bachata (3 one-hour classes): $30; Salsa and Bachata (6 one-hour classes): $50; Drop-ins: $15 per one-hour class

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
